## [§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#capn-proto-runtime-library)Cap’n Proto Runtime Library
This crate contains basic facilities for reading and writing [Cap’n Proto](https://capnproto.org) messages in Rust. It is intended to be used in conjunction with code generated by the [capnpc-rust](https://crates.io/crates/capnpc) crate.
## Modules[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#modules)

[any_pointer](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/any_pointer/index.html "mod capnp::any_pointer")
    Untyped pointer that can be cast to any struct, list, or capability type.

[any_pointer_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/any_pointer_list/index.html "mod capnp::any_pointer_list")
    List of AnyPointers.

[capability](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/capability/index.html "mod capnp::capability")
    Hooks for the RPC system.

[capability_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/capability_list/index.html "mod capnp::capability_list")
    List of capabilities.

[constant](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/constant/index.html "mod capnp::constant")
    Helper type for generated Struct and List constants.

[data](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/data/index.html "mod capnp::data")
    Sequence of bytes.

[data_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/data_list/index.html "mod capnp::data_list")
    List of sequences of bytes.

[dynamic_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/dynamic_list/index.html "mod capnp::dynamic_list")
    Dynamically-typed lists.

[dynamic_struct](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/dynamic_struct/index.html "mod capnp::dynamic_struct")
    Dynamically-typed structs.

[dynamic_value](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/dynamic_value/index.html "mod capnp::dynamic_value")
    Dynamically typed values.

[enum_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/enum_list/index.html "mod capnp::enum_list")
    List of enums.

[introspect](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/introspect/index.html "mod capnp::introspect")
    Traits and types to support run-time type introspection, i.e. reflection.

[io](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/io/index.html "mod capnp::io")
    Custom I/O traits that roughly mirror `std::io::{Read, BufRead, Write}`. This extra layer of indirection enables support of no-std environments.

[list_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/list_list/index.html "mod capnp::list_list")
    List of lists.

[message](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/message/index.html "mod capnp::message")
    Untyped root container for a Cap’n Proto value.

[primitive_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/primitive_list/index.html "mod capnp::primitive_list")
    List of primitives.

[private](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/private/index.html "mod capnp::private")
    Implementation details that should never be directly used by clients.

[raw](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/raw/index.html "mod capnp::raw")
    Functions providing low level access to encoded data.

[schema](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/schema/index.html "mod capnp::schema")
    Convenience wrappers of the datatypes defined in schema.capnp.

[schema_capnp](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/schema_capnp/index.html "mod capnp::schema_capnp")
    Code generated from [schema.capnp](https://github.com/capnproto/capnproto/blob/master/c%2B%2B/src/capnp/schema.capnp).

[serialize](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/serialize/index.html "mod capnp::serialize")
    Reading and writing of messages using the [standard stream framing](https://capnproto.org/encoding.html#serialization-over-a-stream).

[serialize_packed](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/serialize_packed/index.html "mod capnp::serialize_packed")
    Reading and writing of messages using the [packed stream encoding](https://capnproto.org/encoding.html#packing).

[struct_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct_list/index.html "mod capnp::struct_list")
    List of structs.

[text](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/text/index.html "mod capnp::text")
    UTF-8 encoded text.

[text_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/text_list/index.html "mod capnp::text_list")
    List of strings containing UTF-8 encoded text.

[traits](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/traits/index.html "mod capnp::traits")

## Structs[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#structs)

[Error](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct.Error.html "struct capnp::Error")
    Describes an arbitrary error that prevented an operation from completing.

[MessageSize](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct.MessageSize.html "struct capnp::MessageSize")
    Size of a message. Every generated struct has a method `.total_size()` that returns this.

[NotInSchema](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct.NotInSchema.html "struct capnp::NotInSchema")
    An enum value or union discriminant that was not found among those defined in a schema.

[Word](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct.Word.html "struct capnp::Word")
    8 bytes, aligned to an 8-byte boundary.
## Enums[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#enums)

[ErrorKind](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/enum.ErrorKind.html "enum capnp::ErrorKind")
    The general nature of an error. The purpose of this enum is not to describe the error itself, but rather to describe how the client might want to respond to the error.

[OutputSegments](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/enum.OutputSegments.html "enum capnp::OutputSegments")
    Helper struct that allows `MessageBuilder::get_segments_for_output()` to avoid heap allocations in the single-segment case.
## Functions[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#functions)

[word](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/fn.word.html "fn capnp::word")
    Constructs a word with the given bytes.
## Type Aliases[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#types)

[Result](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/type.Result.html "type capnp::Result")
    Because messages are lazily validated, the return type of any method that reads a pointer field must be wrapped in a Result.

## [§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#capn-proto-runtime-library)Cap’n Proto Runtime Library
This crate contains basic facilities for reading and writing [Cap’n Proto](https://capnproto.org) messages in Rust. It is intended to be used in conjunction with code generated by the [capnpc-rust](https://crates.io/crates/capnpc) crate.
## Modules[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#modules)

[any_pointer](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/any_pointer/index.html "mod capnp::any_pointer")
    Untyped pointer that can be cast to any struct, list, or capability type.

[any_pointer_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/any_pointer_list/index.html "mod capnp::any_pointer_list")
    List of AnyPointers.

[capability](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/capability/index.html "mod capnp::capability")
    Hooks for the RPC system.

[capability_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/capability_list/index.html "mod capnp::capability_list")
    List of capabilities.

[constant](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/constant/index.html "mod capnp::constant")
    Helper type for generated Struct and List constants.

[data](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/data/index.html "mod capnp::data")
    Sequence of bytes.

[data_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/data_list/index.html "mod capnp::data_list")
    List of sequences of bytes.

[dynamic_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/dynamic_list/index.html "mod capnp::dynamic_list")
    Dynamically-typed lists.

[dynamic_struct](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/dynamic_struct/index.html "mod capnp::dynamic_struct")
    Dynamically-typed structs.

[dynamic_value](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/dynamic_value/index.html "mod capnp::dynamic_value")
    Dynamically typed values.

[enum_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/enum_list/index.html "mod capnp::enum_list")
    List of enums.

[introspect](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/introspect/index.html "mod capnp::introspect")
    Traits and types to support run-time type introspection, i.e. reflection.

[io](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/io/index.html "mod capnp::io")
    Custom I/O traits that roughly mirror `std::io::{Read, BufRead, Write}`. This extra layer of indirection enables support of no-std environments.

[list_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/list_list/index.html "mod capnp::list_list")
    List of lists.

[message](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/message/index.html "mod capnp::message")
    Untyped root container for a Cap’n Proto value.

[primitive_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/primitive_list/index.html "mod capnp::primitive_list")
    List of primitives.

[private](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/private/index.html "mod capnp::private")
    Implementation details that should never be directly used by clients.

[raw](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/raw/index.html "mod capnp::raw")
    Functions providing low level access to encoded data.

[schema](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/schema/index.html "mod capnp::schema")
    Convenience wrappers of the datatypes defined in schema.capnp.

[schema_capnp](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/schema_capnp/index.html "mod capnp::schema_capnp")
    Code generated from [schema.capnp](https://github.com/capnproto/capnproto/blob/master/c%2B%2B/src/capnp/schema.capnp).

[serialize](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/serialize/index.html "mod capnp::serialize")
    Reading and writing of messages using the [standard stream framing](https://capnproto.org/encoding.html#serialization-over-a-stream).

[serialize_packed](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/serialize_packed/index.html "mod capnp::serialize_packed")
    Reading and writing of messages using the [packed stream encoding](https://capnproto.org/encoding.html#packing).

[struct_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct_list/index.html "mod capnp::struct_list")
    List of structs.

[text](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/text/index.html "mod capnp::text")
    UTF-8 encoded text.

[text_list](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/text_list/index.html "mod capnp::text_list")
    List of strings containing UTF-8 encoded text.

[traits](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/traits/index.html "mod capnp::traits")

## Structs[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#structs)

[Error](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct.Error.html "struct capnp::Error")
    Describes an arbitrary error that prevented an operation from completing.

[MessageSize](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct.MessageSize.html "struct capnp::MessageSize")
    Size of a message. Every generated struct has a method `.total_size()` that returns this.

[NotInSchema](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct.NotInSchema.html "struct capnp::NotInSchema")
    An enum value or union discriminant that was not found among those defined in a schema.

[Word](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/struct.Word.html "struct capnp::Word")
    8 bytes, aligned to an 8-byte boundary.
## Enums[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#enums)

[ErrorKind](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/enum.ErrorKind.html "enum capnp::ErrorKind")
    The general nature of an error. The purpose of this enum is not to describe the error itself, but rather to describe how the client might want to respond to the error.

[OutputSegments](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/enum.OutputSegments.html "enum capnp::OutputSegments")
    Helper struct that allows `MessageBuilder::get_segments_for_output()` to avoid heap allocations in the single-segment case.
## Functions[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#functions)

[word](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/fn.word.html "fn capnp::word")
    Constructs a word with the given bytes.
## Type Aliases[§](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/#types)

[Result](https://docs.rs/capnp/latest/capnp/type.Result.html "type capnp::Result")
